2. **Static Methods**: When used with methods, `static` means that the method belongs to the class itself, rather than any instance of the class. Static methods can be called without creating an instance of the class.

   ```java
public class MyClass {
    public static void myMethod() {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

